Police say a group of eight suspects travelling in two vehicles entered the cargo section of the airport and hijacked a cargo truck. JOHANNESBURG An armed robber has been killed and another arrested in a shootout at OR Tambo International Airport on Saturday morning.Police say a group of eight suspects travelling in two vehicles entered the cargo section of the airport and hijacked a cargo truck.They were confronted by police a few kilometres from the cargo area and a shootout began.It s understood the suspects held up security guards and made off with the truck, which was later recovered in Alexandra township, north of Johannesburg.The other suspects are still at large.Police spokesperson Vishnu Naidoo said, The moment they were arrested, two firearms were recovered, by the looks of things the truck was found with all its goods intact and a vehicle that was hijacked from the airport was also recovered. The case is under investigation. 